				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Does skill mod effect slow %'s?<a name="22076"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 18 04 10:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Haste and Slow are not affected by ANY modifiers, btw.  That includes not only Instruments, but Amplification, Epic, Puretone discipline, Voice of the Serpent etc.
<br />

<br />
If a song has more than one component, the other components MAY be affected by modifiers.  Example:  Amplification and Anthem de Arms gives a LOT of STR.  The Haste is still the same, regardless of Amp or no Amp.  The same for the STR component of the Brass song, McVaxius Beserker Crescendo (lvl 42).  Equipping a Horn will make the STR better, but not the haste.
<br />

<br />
Lvl 48 Chords of Cessation (String, AE Damage and Slow) will do more damage with a Lute equipped, but the Slow is the same regardless of instrument.
<br />

<br />
Hehe.  The short answer is still no, lol.  Now you got the long, and the long LONG answer...</span></td>
