			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yes, JF does indeed raise the slow percentage by a very small amount. This is just because the slow percentage in the requiem of time is not capped at level 65. So when you get that extra 5 levels from JF3, the percentage gets increased.
<br />

<br />
This is why you shouldn't blindly trust the values provided by Lucy. Since Lucy doesn't show the level equations past 65. It shows 52% value for RoT because RoT is 52% when you get it at 64 and 52% when it's &quot;capped&quot; at 65. When in fact the level calculation for RoT would go something like in the chants, say '52% (l64) to 55% (L75)'.
<br />

<br />
And no, I can't offhand remember the exact percentage that RoT gets with JF3. It could be 53% or 55%, I don't remember. But eqcaster has the advantage over Lucy in that it lists all the level calculations for song effects.
<br />

<br />
-Hauta</span></td>
